  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1441792932}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a6f0f20462922ca4ba965d0628704609, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Rules_central_brain_script
  ruleTextDisplay: {fileID: 63065153}
  rulePages:
  - 'Rules

    1, turn stages: rolling

    2, turn stages: Placement

    3, turn
    stages: Typing

    4, turn stages: End

    5, dice: shapes

    6, dice: generic
    structures

    7, dice: special structures

    6, dice: stars

    7, points:
    how to score

    8, points: deductions'
  - 'turn stages: rolling

    At the start of your turn, the dice are cast.

    There
    are 3 structure dice and 3 shape dice, but more on that later.

'
  - "turn stages: Placement\r\nNext, you place your structures on the board.\r\nOn
    the first turn, your structure must overlap your \u201Cstarting point\u201D (a
    small green square on the board)\r\nAfterwards, however, you can place a structure
    anywhere so long as at least one part is adjacent to another structure, and no
    parts are overlapping other structures or river tiles."
  - 'turn stages: Typing

    Players can choose any building type shown on the building
    dice by clicking on one, and any shape shown on the shape dice by clicking on
    one, more on the specific in the dice segment.

'
  - 'turn stages: End

    Once each player has placed a structure (or is unable
    to or announces the end of the game), the turn ends.

'
  - "dice: shapes\r\nThere are 6 shapes on the dice.\r\na 1x1 square, \r\na 2x2 square,
    \r\na 3x2 T shape, \r\na 3x2 z shape,\r\na 4x1 I shape,\r\nand finally a 3x2
    L shape.\r\nA shape only dictates the shape of the structure that will be placed
    on the board, and has no direct impact on the scoring.\r\n"
  - "dice: generic structures\r\nThere are 3 generic structures:\r\nR: Residential\r\nI:
    Industrial\r\nC: Commercial\r\nThe basic structure types and connected structures
    of the same type are worth a set number of points, as shown in the \u201Cpoints:
    how to score\u201D section.\r\n"
  - "dice: generic structures\r\nThere are 3 generic structures:\r\nR: Residential\r\nI:
    Industrial\r\nC: Commercial\r\nThe basic structure types and connected structures
    of the same type are worth a set number of points, as shown in the \u201Cpoints:
    how to score\u201D section.\r\ndice: special structures\r\nThere are 3 types
    of special structures:\r\nstick figure: school\r\nYou gain 1 point for each structure
    within connected structure chains\r\ntree: park\r\nYou gain 1 point for each
    different connected structure type\r\nwaves: river\r\nThe structure must be connected
    to the river. Though it doesn't have to be connected to your structures. You
    can choose any building type when making the structure, but the shape is selected
    from the shape die.\r\n"
  - 'dice: stars

    If two of the dice match, a star will appear on them. Stars
    are worth 1 bonus point each when scoring at the end!

'
